            <fr:title text="Quicksort by Löb induction">Quicksort by Löb induction</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Sort a finite <html:em>multiset</html:em> — so that "same contents" is an
equation of bags — following
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectSorting2025/" title="Intrinsically Correct Sorting in Cubical Agda" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectSorting2025/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectSorting2025/" type="local">intrinsically correct sorting</fr:link>
and
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectAlgorithms2025-preprint/" title="Intrinsically Correct Algorithms and Recursive Coalgebras" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectAlgorithms2025-preprint/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectAlgorithms2025-preprint/" type="local">Alexandru, Urbat, and Wißmann</fr:link>.
Over bags measured by size, the functor of subproblems is
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[H X\,{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left (b = \varnothing \right )\mathclose {}}
   \;+\; \sum _{b \,=\, \mathit {lo} + {\mathopen {}\left \{p\right \}\mathclose {}} + \mathit {hi}}
   X{\mathopen {}\left (\mathit {lo}\right )\mathclose {}} \times  X{\mathopen {}\left (\mathit {hi}\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
the sum ranging over pivot decompositions with
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathit {lo} \le  p \le  \mathit {hi}]]></fr:tex> and
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathit {lo}, \mathit {hi} \prec  b]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>The coalgebra partitions at a pivot. The algebra concatenates
sorted lists,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (l, r\right )\mathclose {}} \;\mapsto \;
   l \mathbin {++} {\mathopen {}\left  [p\right  ]\mathclose {}} \mathbin {++} r,]]></fr:tex>
spending the bounds at the seams and the recombination equation on
the contents.</html:p>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> of this coalgebra and algebra is
quicksort, sorted and content-preserving by the type of its result —
and by <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" title="Recursive coalgebras and corecursive algebras" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" type="local">uniqueness</fr:link>, <html:em>any</html:em> function satisfying the
recurrence is this one.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
